{
  "text": "where x i+1 denotes the perturbed sample at (i+1) th iteration. While there has been extensive work in this area [Yuan et al., 2019; [CITATION_1] , we primarily focus our attention towards attacks which utilizes latent layer representation. [CITATION_2] proposed a method to construct adversarial perturbation by manipulating the latent layer of different classes. However, Latent Attack (LA) exploits the adversarial vulnerability of the latent layers to compute adversarial perturbations.",
